#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""chatgpt-imagegen — generate images using your ChatGPT subscription, no API key.

Two backends produce the same kind of bitmap, but bill different buckets:

  * web (default): drives your already-logged-in ChatGPT browser via
    `agent-browser`, generating on the ChatGPT *conversation* surface. The real
    browser clears Cloudflare + the sentinel proof-of-work a headless client
    cannot replicate. This does NOT consume the metered Codex-usage limit —
    it's the same surface as typing in the app. Needs a logged-in browser open.

  * codex: a headless POST to `chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex/responses` with the
    `image_generation` tool, reusing the OAuth token from `~/.codex/auth.json`
    (`codex login`). Fast and dependency-free, but every call bills the metered
    Codex-usage bucket.

Usage:
    chatgpt-imagegen "a watercolor cat"                       # web backend (default)
    chatgpt-imagegen "logo" -o brand/logo.png --size 1024x1024
    chatgpt-imagegen "hero banner" -o web/hero.png --backend codex

Setup (one-time):
    web backend:   install agent-browser-stealth (provides the `agent-browser`
                   command) and connect its extension to your logged-in Chrome;
                   be signed in to chatgpt.com in that browser.
    codex backend: `npm i -g @openai/codex` and run `codex login`.

Project: https://github.com/leeguooooo/chatgpt-imagegen
"""
